#{{mineralogy}} A body of [[igneous]] [[rock]] formed beneath the surface of the earth by [[consolidation]] of [[magma]]
#{{astronomy}} Any trans-Neptunian [[planet]]; specifically, any planet whose orbit is more highly inclined and elliptical than that of traditional planets, and which takes more than 200 Julian years to revolve around its sun. 
#: ''[[Pluto]], its companion [[Charon]]{{,}} and the object nicknamed [[Xena]] are all '''plutons'''.''

